article.headline: Jacksonville St. 57, Morehead St. 52
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Nick Smith hit two free throws with four seconds left as Jacksonville State beat Morehead State 57-52 Tuesday night. Shaun Williams pulled Morehead State (10-15, 6-11 Ohio Valley Conference) to within two points at 54-52, hitting two free throws with 16 seconds left. Harold Crow's run-out dunk on the inbounds play for Jacksonville (8-18, 6-11) with 13 seconds to go gave the Gamecocks a 56-52 lead. Morehead State had the ball but missed a 3-pointer, setting up Smith's free throws. Smith finished with 16 points for Jacksonville, Crow had 14 and Erik Adams 10. Cordaryl Ballard scored 11 for Morehead State, and Shaun Williams had 10 points and 13 rebounds. The Eagles lost their ninth straight, shooting 21-of-61 (34.4 percent) from the field, including 0-of-17 from 3-point range. The Gamecocks were 20-of-48 (41.7 percent) and 5-of-19 on 3-pointers.
